    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="703" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d703">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 27,
                                    1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 740.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I inclose for your information and files a
                            copy of a letter from the Navy Department embodying telegraphic
                            instructions sent on the 17th instant to Bear-Admiral Selfridge in
                            regard to the protection of American citizens by our naval vessels in
                            Turkish waters.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Richard Olney.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <opener>
                        <seg rendition="#center">[Inclosure in No. 740.]</seg>
                    </opener>
                    <head>
                        <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">McAdoo</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                    </head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <placeName>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Navy Department</hi>,<lb/>
                                <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                            </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-18">
                                <hi rend="italic">December 18,
                                        1895</hi>
                            </date>.</dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that
                                the following instructions were cabled on the 7th instant to the
                                commander in chief of the United States naval force on the European
                                station at Mersina, Syria: <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>The <hi rend="italic">Minneapolis</hi> ordered to
                                        Alexandretta, Syria, Marash, Turkey, center of danger.
                                        Suggest the concentration of vessels United States Navy, and
                                        taking missionaries and other Americans on board, if
                                        necessary. Act promptly if in your judgment advisable to
                                        land force. Keep Department fully informed. Acknowledge.</p>
                            <p rend="right">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Herbert.</hi>
                            </p>
                        </quote>
                    </p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">W. McAdoo.</hi>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
